{
    "name": "Pyric Heliacus",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A few sapient pyric revenants master the spiritual fires within them, becoming pyric heliacuses instead of pyric wraiths. With phenomenal mental discipline, a heliacus can bend fire and light, including cutting victims off from warmth and sight. Heliacuses hunger for knowledge as much as flesh and spirit, so they converse with other beings and seek out repositories of lore. However, heliacuses are imperious and malevolent, consuming anyone who fails to edify or impress them.<br/><br/>As a heliacus\u2019s enlightenment grows, so does its body, until the creature tops 12 feet. However, as little more than flame, skin, and bone, a heliacus weighs only 300 pounds."
        }
    ],
